{"parentUuid":"75c52ae6-fc53-4d79-8ae4-e79185f15c27","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/thies/Projects/GitHub/Sandcastle","sessionId":"26d46785-2e10-478d-9642-9a0894786c64","version":"2.1.50","gitBranch":"main","slug":"merry-dreaming-blossom","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XFViPL9QDBg6bq6LfXmX5j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Internet is working.** Now you need to go through the Tailscale login flow in the web UI to authenticate the sidecar (it's in `pending` state). Here's what was wrong and what was fixed:\n\n---\n\n**Root cause:** `DOCKYARD_POOL_BASE` was missing from `/sandcastle/.env`. The installer wrote it to `sandcastle.env` but not `.env`, so docker-compose fell back to its hardcoded default `10.89.0.0/16`. When `TailscaleManager#subnet_for` generated a random `/24`, it picked from `10.89.x.x` — **outside** the iptables `MASQUERADE` rule (which only covers `10.206.0.0/16`). The sidecar had no NAT, so all outbound traffic was silently dropped.\n\n**Live fix:**\n1. Appended `DOCKYARD_POOL_BASE=10.206.0.0/16` to `/sandcastle/.env`\n2. Force-recreated web + worker containers (`DOCKYARD_POOL_BASE` is now `10.206.0.0/16` inside Rails)\n3. Restarted Tailscale login flow — new sidecar got subnet `10.206.57.0/24` ✓\n\n**Installer fix (committed):** `DOCKYARD_POOL_BASE` is now written into the fresh-install `.env` heredoc AND backfilled in both the install and update paths, so this can never happen again.\n\nGo to the Tailscale settings page and complete the login flow to finish authenticating the sidecar."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":341,"cache_read_input_tokens":76449,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":341},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CYMZAur75NnS3HaUkj7cS","type":"assistant","uuid":"e2abee43-399a-4ef9-ae7